  "body": "version    1.9.12-stable-b6f1c8dc\r\n\r\nIs it possible to recover from Failed to write block into disk ?\r\n\r\n```\r\nFailed to write block into disk          err=\"open chaindata/005781.log: operation not permitted\"\r\n```\r\nThis was a temporary glitch I believe from my side and would be nice if restarting Geth, it was possible to recover from this point in time.\r\n\r\nThe next runs of Geth stop with fatal error:\r\n```\r\nINFO [04-18|16:46:53.616] Initialised chain configuration          config=\"{ChainID: 5 Homestead: 0 DAO: <nil> DAOSupport: true EIP150: 0 EIP155: 0 EIP158: 0 Byzantium: \r\n0 Constantinople: 0 Petersburg: 0 Istanbul: 1561651, Muir Glacier: <nil>, Engine: clique}\"\r\nINFO [04-18|16:46:53.685] Initialising Ethereum protocol           versions=\"[65 64 63]\" network=5 dbversion=7\r\nWARN [04-18|16:46:53.695] Head state missing, repairing chain      number=2544958 hash=96b909…8f0bd9\r\nINFO [04-18|16:46:53.875] Deep froze chain segment                 blocks=177 elapsed=285.522ms number=2454957 hash=85b977…198956\r\nFatal: Error starting protocol stack: missing block 2528964 [4b2c917702ba5c14eaf0823f2b28750f1a8fe86834ef562eff9b5eb3cdc4c4a1]\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd the next one:\r\n```\r\nINFO [04-18|16:47:53.459] Initialising Ethereum protocol           versions=\"[65 64 63]\" network=5 dbversion=7\r\nWARN [04-18|16:47:53.463] Head state missing, repairing chain      number=2544958 hash=96b909…8f0bd9\r\nFatal: Error starting protocol stack: missing block 2529790 [9f09e359ef15dfbd29840cfd50de5acfa09029e5205ccf22fb1933afff53d965]\r\n```\r\n\r\nIs there a way to tell Geth to (re)request peers for the missing block/s, rather than giving up immediately?",
